wiki.summary: “Em Calls Paul” is, as the title suggests, is a skit about Eminem returning Paul’s call that played during "Encore"’s previous skit. Eminem addresses his situation with Michael Jackson and the “Just Lose It” video. These skits were recorded after the controversial aforementioned song and its music video were released ahead Encore’s release. While the video itself wasn’t explicit, it did parody Michael Jackson heavily. Eminem utilizes a voice modulator box known as a Electrolarynx throughout the skit. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “Em Calls Paul” is, as the title suggests, is a skit about Eminem returning Paul’s call that played during "Encore"’s previous skit. Eminem addresses his situation with Michael Jackson and the “Just Lose It” video. These skits were recorded after the controversial aforementioned song and its music video were released ahead Encore’s release. While the video itself wasn’t explicit, it did parody Michael Jackson heavily. Eminem utilizes a voice modulator box known as a Electrolarynx throughout the skit. Electrolarynx’s are for those who are incapable of speaking normally through the mouth. It still remains unclear why Eminem did this. Read more on Last.fm.
